In [9]:
fwhm_maj = (radio[0].header['BMAJ']+1./3600.)*u.degree
fwhm_min = (radio[0].header['BMIN']+1./3600.)*u.degree
pa = (radio[0].header['BPA']+90.)*u.degree
size_pix = abs(radio[0].header['CDELT1'])*u.degree
amplitude = 1./2./numpy.pi/(fwhm_maj/2.355/size_pix)/(fwhm_min/2.355/size_pix)
psf = Gaussian2D(amplitude = amplitude, x_stddev = fwhm_maj/2.355/size_pix, y_stddev = fwhm_min/2.355/size_pix,
                 theta = pa.to(u.radian))
